You can do the following:

Create an instance of your `AmountHandler` for every variation you require in the same place where you define your `StreamBuilder`, for example:

    AmountHandler amountHandler10_2 = new AmountHandler(10, 2);
    AmountHandler amountHandler3_1 = new AmountHandler(3, 1);

You then register each instance with the `StreamBuilder`:

    final StreamBuilder builder = new StreamBuilder(&quot;builder_name&quot;)
      .format(&quot;xml&quot;)
      .addTypeHandler(&quot;amountHandler10_2&quot;, amountHandler10_2)
      .addTypeHandler(&quot;amountHandler3_1&quot;, amountHandler3_1)
      .addRecord(CustomField.class);


Then you reference the appropriate type handler on each `@Field`, using the name you have given the instance when registering it with the `StreamBuilder` and using the `handlerName` property instead of `handlerClass`:

    @Field(ordinal = 2, length = 8, padding = &#39;0&#39;, align = Align.RIGHT, handlerName = &quot;amountHandler10_2&quot;)
    private BigDecimal firstAmount;
    @Field(ordinal = 3, length = 8, padding = &#39;0&#39;, align = Align.RIGHT, handlerName = &quot;amountHandler3_1&quot;)
